content: The Lord’s Glory and Man’s Dignity.
To the Chief Musician; set to a Philistine lute [or perhaps to a particular Hittite tune]. A Psalm of David.
How majestic  glorious  excellent is Your name in all the earth!
You have displayed Your splendor above the heavens.
Out of the mouths of infants and nursing babes You have established strength
That You might silence the enemy  make the revengeful cease.
